==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inertion
<hw>In*er"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Lack of activity or
exertion; inertness; quietude.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These vicissitudes of exertion and <qex>inertion</qex> of the
arterial system constitute the paroxysms of remittent fever.</q>
<rj><qau>E. Darwin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inertitude</ent>⟦br⟧
